column3: Most modern microprocessors have at least one of these features in their CPU design to make debugging easier.

column1: types of debugger in system programming
column3: An instruction set that meets the Popek and Goldberg virtualization requirements makes it easier to write debugger software that runs on the same CPU as the software being debugged  such a CPU can execute the inner loops of the program under test at full speed, and still remain under debugger control.
